title: For Sale:  Pre-ban M1A National Match --- Custom ---
postcontent:
Up for sale is my like new custom Pre-ban Springfield Armory M1A, set up in a National Match configuration. 

First off, lets start with the basics. The receiver is an early Springfield M1A, definitely Pre-Ban, most likely built in the late 1980s. It was a "Green Box" gun, making it rare, and the most desirable generation of M1A. Serial number is 069,xxx. 

This gun has a handmade match weight walnut stock, with tiger stripe/curly blonde grain, and has had tung oil applied by hand. It is incredible. Was made and installed by the previous owner who made custom stocks for a living.

Also, it has a Krieger Super Match stainless steel heavy barrel. This barrel is tight enough to pop primers, and it does not get any more accurate than this one in an M1A. (Fitting alone by Krieger was almost $300, not including the cost of the barrel itself).

TRW bolt, HRA Op Rod, NM internals. All the best parts. 

This rifle also has National Match sights, making the use of iron sights out to 600 meters possible. Also has a picatinny rail on the forend of the stock which will make mounting a bipod easy. Match grade trigger is as crisp as any I have ever felt, and breaks like glass at around 3# or so.

Included is a Springfield Armory picatinny style scope mount ($150), a Bushnell 4-16 scope with BDC ($150), Weaver rings, and a 20 round mag.

This gun has EXACTLY 40 rounds down the tube. 1/2 MOA is like walking the dog with this gun, and it is not even broken in yet.

I am asking $2,800 or best reasonable offer, no trades unless its something pretty damn cool, and about $2,000 cash on top.

Located in Fayetteville.

Call or text 479-439-two191 or email through Armslist

title: For Sale:  Concealed Weapons Permit Class (aka Concealed Carry Course) for $59
postcontent:
One of the requirements by the State of Florida to apply for a concealed weapons permit is to have successfully taken a concealed carry course under a certified instructor. Miami Shooters Club provides such a course with its team of NRA certified instructors - who will teach students the important fundamentals of how to safely use a semi-automatic pistol and revolver. Your concealed weapons permit will allow you to concealed carry in more than 30 states.

Miami Shooters Club's instructors carry multiple certifications under the NRA, have traveled abroad to train and receive firearm certifications, and are hand-to-hand self defense experts - having taught multiple seminars for the Miami Dade Police Department. Under their instruction in the concealed carry class, students will learn the mechanisms behind pistols and how they operate while learning how to grip the firearm, aim, pull the trigger, get into a proper stance, and much more. The class also covers many of the legal issues and expected ethics of concealed carry in Florida. The classes are designed for complete beginners who have never touched a gun before... but experienced shooters will learn something as well.

At the end of the classroom portion, students will safely discharge a pistol under the supervision of a certified instructor, as required by the State of Florida. Miami Shooters Club will provide a firearm, ammunition, eye protection, and ear protection at no extra cost.

Classes take place in Miami on Fridays at 6:30pm or on Saturdays at 1pm.
